{{BLP sources|date=January 2017}}
'''Shigeru Iitaka''' (飯高 茂 Iitaka Shigeru, born May 29, 1942, [[Chiba, Chiba|Chiba]]) is a Japanese mathematician at [[Gakushuin University]] working in algebraic geometry who introduced the [[Kodaira dimension]] and [[Iitaka dimension]].

He received in 1970 his Ph.D. from the [[University of Tokyo]] under [[Kunihiko Kodaira]] with thesis「代数多様体のD-次元について」(''On D-dimensions of algebraic varieties'').<ref>{{MathGenealogy|id=188665}}</ref> He was awarded the [[Iyanaga Prize]] of the Mathematical Society of Japan in 1980 
and the [[Japan Academy Prize (academics)|Japan Academy Prize]] in 1990.

